# AI-Assisted Python Programming: Running Example

This document describes a Python application that students will build in the course. The application will be implemented in Python using the ``Dash`` package for building web applications.

The application is about creating, taking, and analyzing surveys. It has the following features:

* Survey builder. Used by the investigator to construct surveys by specifying questions and the type of answers (e.g., "yes/no", short answer).
* Survey taker. Used by a survey participant to enter their information. When submitted, the results are stored by the application.
* Survey analyzer. Generates reports on the survey results.
